        intro: "Engineered wood products like Cross-Laminated Timber (CLT) and Glued Laminated Timber (Glulam) are reshaping the scene of multi-family projects. These materials provide superior strength and stability compared to traditional lumber. The industry has seen a fundamental change toward environmentally responsible building practices in high-density mid-rise developments. Construction schedules are shorter and carbon footprints are smaller.\n\nSetSquare has been Vancouver's leading timber framer for 15 years. We specialize in multi-family homes and multi-unit projects. Our team knows how to navigate complex building codes and implement rigorous quality assurance protocols that will give exceptional results. Building Information Modeling (BIM) and advanced construction techniques help us deliver both esthetic appeal and structural excellence.",
        highlightBox: "The case for timber in multi-family construction has gone from theoretical to proven. Buildings are standing. Tenants are living in them. The data on cost, speed, and performance is real.",
