        category: "Residential",
        subtitle: "What homeowners who've built in timber know that most people don't",
        intro: "Call it a best-kept secret if you like, though the people who've built in timber and lived in the result aren't exactly keeping quiet about it. There's something that happens when you spend time inside a well-built timber frame home that's genuinely hard to explain - a sense of solidity, of warmth, of a building that feels considered rather than just assembled. This piece is about why that feeling is real, and what's actually behind it.",
        highlightBox: "People who build timber frame homes and then sell them almost always tell us the same thing: they wish they hadn't sold. That's not marketing. That's what owners actually say.",
