                content: "Multi-storey residential projects are where layout discipline has the most leverage. A half-inch error in wall position on the ground floor becomes a half-inch error in room dimensions on the second floor and a potential alignment problem for the stair enclosure and the mechanical chase. These things do not self-correct as you go up.\n\nFramers who have worked on 4-6 storey wood-frame buildings understand this compounding dynamic and manage layout accordingly. They establish and maintain clean reference points at every level and verify that the structure above matches the structure below before proceeding. In the Lower Mainland market, this is increasingly standard expectation for mid-density residential."
